   "source": [
    "# 🔍 BM25 vs Embeddings: Why Keyword Search Still Wins for Product Data\n",
    "\n",
    "> *Based on: [BM25 vs Embeddings — ai.rs, Jan 29 2026](https://ai.rs)*\n",
    "\n",
    "Every AI tutorial tells you to use embedding search: convert your data to vectors, store them in a vector database, and enjoy "semantic understanding" that keyword search can't match.\n",
    "\n",
    "**But when both approaches were tested against a real product catalog, the results told a different story.**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook walks you through:\n",
    "1. What BM25 is and how it works (the math, simply)\n",
    "2. A hands-on implementation — from scratch, in ~30 lines\n",
    "3. A live comparison: BM25 vs embedding similarity on product queries\n",
    "4. When to use each — and when to combine them\n",
    "\n",
    "**No GPU. No model downloads. No API keys needed.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📦 Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "BM25 needs only the Python standard library. We'll add `sentence-transformers` for the embedding comparison section."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# BM25 needs nothing — it's pure Python\n",
    "# Install sentence-transformers only for the embedding comparison later\n",
    "!pip install sentence-transformers --quiet"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. What is BM25?\n",
    "\n",
    "**BM25** (Best Matching 25) is a ranking function used by search engines to rank documents by relevance to a query. It's the algorithm behind Elasticsearch, Solr, and Lucene.\n",
    "\n",
    "It builds on **TF-IDF** (term frequency × inverse document frequency) but adds two corrections:\n",
    "\n",
    "### The Formula\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{score}(D, Q) = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} \\text{IDF}(q_i) \\cdot \\frac{f(q_i, D) \\cdot (k_1 + 1)}{f(q_i, D) + k_1 \\cdot \\left(1 - b + b \\cdot \\frac{|D|}{\\text{avgdl}}\\right)}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where:\n",
    "- $q_i$ = each term in the query\n",
    "- $f(q_i, D)$ = how often $q_i$ appears in document $D$ (term frequency)\n",
    "- $|D|$ = length of document $D$ (word count)\n",
    "- $\\text{avgdl}$ = average document length across the corpus\n",
    "- $k_1$ ≈ 1.5 → controls term frequency saturation (doubling occurrences doesn't double the score)\n",
    "- $b$ ≈ 0.75 → controls length normalization (long documents don't unfairly dominate)\n",
    "\n",
    "### The IDF component\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{IDF}(q_i) = \\log\\left(\\frac{N - n(q_i) + 0.5}{n(q_i) + 0.5} + 1\\right)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where $N$ = total documents, $n(q_i)$ = documents containing the term.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Common words** (\"the\", \"a\") appear everywhere → low IDF → low weight.  \n",
    "**Rare words** (\"BM25\", \"Merlot\") appear rarely → high IDF → high weight."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 2. BM25 from Scratch — 30 Lines"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import math\n",
    "from collections import Counter\n",
    "\n",
    "class BM25:\n",
    "    def __init__(self, documents, k1=1.5, b=0.75):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        documents: list of strings (one per document)\n",
    "        k1: term frequency saturation (1.2–2.0 typical)\n",
    "        b:  length normalization (0 = no normalization, 1 = full)\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        self.k1, self.b = k1, b\n",
    "        self.docs = documents\n",
    "        self.avgdl = sum(len(d.split()) for d in documents) / len(documents)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Document frequency: how many docs contain each term\n",
    "        self.df = Counter()\n",
    "        for doc in documents:\n",
    "            for term in set(doc.lower().split()):\n",
    "                self.df[term] += 1\n",
    "        self.N = len(documents)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def score(self, query, doc_idx):\n",
    "        doc = self.docs[doc_idx].lower().split()\n",
    "        doc_len = len(doc)\n",
    "        tf = Counter(doc)\n",
    "        score = 0\n",
    "        for term in query.lower().split():\n",
    "            if term not in self.df:\n",
    "                continue\n",
    "            idf = math.log((self.N - self.df[term] + 0.5) / (self.df[term] + 0.5) + 1)\n",
    "            term_tf = tf.get(term, 0)\n",
    "            score += idf * (term_tf * (self.k1 + 1)) / (\n",
    "                term_tf + self.k1 * (1 - self.b + self.b * doc_len / self.avgdl)\n",
    "            )\n",
    "        return score\n",
    "\n",
    "    def search(self, query, top_k=5):\n",
    "        scores = [(i, self.score(query, i)) for i in range(self.N)]\n",
    "        return sorted(scores, key=lambda x: -x[1])[:top_k]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ BM25 class ready — no dependencies, no GPU\")"
   ]
  },
  {
