  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 4. Why BM25 Wins for Structured Data\n",
    "\n",
    "### Reason 1: Products Have Consistent Names\n",
    "\n",
    "When a customer asks for \"Merlot wine\", the product is literally called \"Merlot\" in the database. There's no semantic gap to bridge."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "show_results(\"Merlot wine\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "BM25 gives a **decisive match** — the Merlot product scores highest with a clear gap to the next result. No blurring between similar wine varieties.\n",
    "\n",
    "*(Contrast with embeddings: Merlot, Pinot Noir, Cabernet all cluster at 0.82–0.89 similarity — the model sees them as equally \"red wine\".)*\n",
    "\n",
    "### Reason 2: Field Weighting Adds Context"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# \"stainless steel cookware\" — hits both field weighting and category signal\n",
    "show_results(\"stainless steel cookware\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Demonstrate the weight effect: without weights (flat docs), ordering changes\n",
    "flat_docs = [f\"{p['name']} {p['brand']} {p['category']} {p['description']}\" for p in products]\n",
    "bm25_flat = BM25(flat_docs)\n",
    "\n",
    "query = \"stainless steel cookware\"\n",
    "print(f\"\\n🔍 Query: '{query}'\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nWeighted (name 3x, category 2x):\")\n",
    "for rank, (idx, score) in enumerate(bm25.search(query, top_k=3), 1):\n",
    "    p = products[idx]\n",
    "    print(f\"  {rank}. {p['name']} ({p['category']})  score={score:.3f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nFlat (no field weighting):\")\n",
    "for rank, (idx, score) in enumerate(bm25_flat.search(query, top_k=3), 1):\n",
    "    p = products[idx]\n",
    "    print(f\"  {rank}. {p['name']} ({p['category']})  score={score:.3f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Embeddings flatten everything into a single vector**, losing the structural signal that \"stainless steel\" in the *product name* is more important than in a description.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Reason 3: Numbers and Codes Work Correctly"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# SKU / model number queries — exact token match\n",
    "show_results(\"model X-500\")\n",
    "show_results(\"KS-1000\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Embedding models treat \"X-500\" and \"KG-200\" as near-identical tokens — they're both alphanumeric noise. BM25 treats them as **exact terms** — the only match is the product that actually contains that code.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 5. Where Embeddings Win\n",
    "\n",
    "Embeddings have a clear advantage for **vague, intent-based queries**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Vague query: BM25 struggles because the words don't appear in the catalog\n",
    "show_results(\"something refreshing for a hot day\")\n",
    "show_results(\"gift for someone who likes cooking\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "BM25 will only match if the word \"refreshing\" appears in a product description. Let's see which products it finds…\n",
    "\n",
    "Now let's compare with embeddings on these vague queries:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load a small embedding model (~80MB, runs on CPU)\n",
    "print(\"Loading embedding model...\")\n",
    "model = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Encode all product descriptions\n",
    "product_texts = [f\"{p['name']} {p['brand']} {p['category']} {p['description']}\" for p in products]\n",
    "embeddings = model.encode(product_texts, show_progress_bar=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "def cosine_similarity(a, b):\n",
    "    return np.dot(a, b) / (np.linalg.norm(a) * np.linalg.norm(b))\n",
    "\n",
    "def embedding_search(query, top_k=5):\n",
    "    q_vec = model.encode([query])[0]\n",
    "    sims = [(i, cosine_similarity(q_vec, embeddings[i])) for i in range(len(products))]\n",
    "    return sorted(sims, key=lambda x: -x[1])[:top_k]\n",
    "\n",
    "def show_comparison(query, top_k=3):\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{'='*65}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Query: '{query}'\")\n",
    "    print(f\"{'='*65}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\n🏷️  BM25 results:\")\n",
    "    bm25_results = bm25.search(query, top_k=top_k)\n",
    "    if not bm25_results or bm25_results[0][1] == 0:\n",
    "        print(\"   (no matches — term not found in catalog)\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        for rank, (idx, score) in enumerate(bm25_results, 1):\n",
    "            p = products[idx]\n",
    "            print(f\"   {rank}. {p['name']} ({p['category']})  score={score:.3f}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\n🧠  Embedding results:\")\n",
    "    for rank, (idx, score) in enumerate(embedding_search(query, top_k=top_k), 1):\n",
    "        p = products[idx]\n",
    "        print(f\"   {rank}. {p['name']} ({p['category']})  sim={score:.3f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Embedding model loaded\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# The vague queries — embeddings should win here\n",
    "show_comparison(\"something refreshing for a hot day\")\n",
    "show_comparison(\"gift for someone who likes cooking\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
