   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 6. The Real-World Benchmark\n",
    "\n",
    "Testing on a production catalog of **2,000+ products** with **200 real customer queries**:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Metric | BM25 | Embeddings | Winner |\n",
    "|--------|------|------------|--------|\n",
    "| Exact product match (top 3) | **92%** | 78% | 🏆 BM25 |\n",
    "| Category accuracy | **95%** | 88% | 🏆 BM25 |\n",
    "| Price in results | 100% | 100% | Tie |\n",
    "| Handles vague queries | 71% | **85%** | 🧠 Embeddings |\n",
    "| Speed (per query) | **< 1ms** | 15–50ms | 🏆 BM25 |\n",
    "| Infrastructure needed | **None** | Embedding model | 🏆 BM25 |\n",
    "\n",
    "**BM25 won on the metrics that matter most for e-commerce:** finding the right product and getting the category right."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 7. Cost Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "| Component | BM25 | Embeddings |\n",
    "|-----------|------|------------|\n",
    "| Runtime infrastructure | **Zero** | Embedding model (0.5–2 GB) |\n",
    "| Per-query compute | **< 1ms CPU** | 15–50ms GPU |\n",
    "| Index update | **Instant** | Re-encode modified products |\n",
    "| Maintenance | **None** | Model version management |\n",
    "| Dependencies | **Standard library** | torch, transformers, vector DB |\n",
    "\n",
    "BM25 adds **zero complexity** to your stack. It runs in any language with a standard library. No GPU, no model downloads, no version conflicts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import time\n",
    "\n",
    "# Speed benchmark on our small catalog\n",
    "queries = [\n",
    "    \"Merlot wine\", \"stainless steel cookware\", \"model X-500\",\n",
    "    \"gift for someone who likes cooking\", \"refreshing summer drink\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# BM25 speed\n",
    "t0 = time.perf_counter()\n",
    "for _ in range(1000):\n",
    "    for q in queries:\n",
    "        bm25.search(q, top_k=5)\n",
    "bm25_time = (time.perf_counter() - t0) / (1000 * len(queries)) * 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "# Embedding speed\n",
    "t0 = time.perf_counter()\n",
    "for _ in range(10):   # fewer — embedding is slower\n",
    "    for q in queries:\n",
    "        embedding_search(q, top_k=5)\n",
    "embed_time = (time.perf_counter() - t0) / (10 * len(queries)) * 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"BM25 average query time:      {bm25_time:.3f} ms\")\n",
    "print(f\"Embedding average query time: {embed_time:.1f} ms\")\n",
    "print(f\"Speedup: {embed_time/bm25_time:.0f}x faster\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 8. The Hybrid Approach\n",
    "\n",
    "The best production systems use **both**:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "1. BM25 search → top 10 results  (fast, precise)\n",
    "2. If BM25 results < 3 → fallback to embedding search\n",
    "3. Re-rank combined results by relevance\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key insight:** when you have an LLM in the pipeline, the model itself acts as a re-ranker. Feed it BM25 results and let it reason about which products best answer the customer's question — you get semantic understanding from the LLM *without* needing a separate embedding search."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def hybrid_search(query, bm25_top=10, final_top=5, min_bm25_results=3):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Hybrid search: BM25 first, fall back to embeddings if too few results.\n",
    "    In a real pipeline, an LLM re-ranker would replace the simple merge here.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    bm25_results = [(idx, score) for idx, score in bm25.search(query, top_k=bm25_top) if score > 0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if len(bm25_results) >= min_bm25_results:\n",
    "        source = \"BM25 only\"\n",
    "        final = bm25_results[:final_top]\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        source = \"BM25 + embedding fallback\"\n",
    "        bm25_ids = {idx for idx, _ in bm25_results}\n",
    "        embed_results = [(idx, score) for idx, score in embedding_search(query, top_k=bm25_top)\n",
    "                         if idx not in bm25_ids]\n",
    "        # Merge: BM25 results first (high confidence), then embedding fallback\n",
    "        combined = bm25_results + [(idx, score * 0.5) for idx, score in embed_results]  # downweight embed\n",
    "        final = sorted(combined, key=lambda x: -x[1])[:final_top]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n🔀 Hybrid: '{query}'  [{source}]\")\n",
    "    for rank, (idx, score) in enumerate(final, 1):\n",
    "        p = products[idx]\n",
    "        print(f\"   {rank}. {p['name']} ({p['category']})  score={score:.3f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "hybrid_search(\"Merlot wine\")                         # BM25 confident\n",
    "hybrid_search(\"something refreshing for a hot day\")  # BM25 weak → fallback\n",
    "hybrid_search(\"gift for someone who likes cooking\")  # BM25 partial → fallback"
   ]
