    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 9. When to Use What\n",
    "\n",
    "| Scenario | Recommendation |\n",
    "|----------|---------------|\n",
    "| Structured product catalog | **BM25** |\n",
    "| FAQ / documentation search | Embeddings |\n",
    "| Multi-language product search | BM25 + aliases |\n",
    "| Conversational discovery | Embeddings (or LLM re-ranking) |\n",
    "| Real-time (< 5ms) | **BM25** |\n",
    "| Budget-constrained | **BM25** |\n",
    "| Unstructured knowledge base | Embeddings |\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 10. Key Takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Start with BM25.** Simpler, faster, more accurate for structured product data.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Add field weighting.** Name (3x), brand (2x), category (2x), description (1x) — this alone gets you to 90%+ accuracy.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **BM25 handles codes and SKUs** that embeddings treat as noise.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **Embeddings win on vague intent** — \"something refreshing for a hot day\" requires semantic understanding.\n",
    "\n",
    "5. **The hybrid is best** — BM25 as the primary retriever, embedding fallback for vague queries, LLM as re-ranker.\n",
    "\n",
    "6. **Zero extra infrastructure.** BM25 is a 30-line Python class with no dependencies. Embeddings need a model, GPU (ideally), and a vector store.\n",
